title: Can anyone help place these lyrics, “I have seen things a girl ain't supposed to see” song is from the late 80's, possibly early 90's? - Quora

response.answer_text: If you’ve slightly misquoted a lyric that actually goes — I've been undressed by kings and I've seen some thingsThat a woman ain't s'posed to see —then it’s “I’ve Never Been To Me” by Charlene. I've Never Been To me lyrics If that’s not the one you want, be advised that you can Google for the lyrics you remember. Put them inside quotes, and if you’re not sure of any word(s), leave them out and break the line into multiple quoted pieces. For instance, if you felt that you weren’t sure if the lyric above said “woman” or “girl”, nor how “s’posed” were spelled (it might be the full word, “supposed”), you could Google it “either way” by phrasing your search as: “That a” “ain’t” “posed to see” Also, if you know the tune and can at least somewhat carry a tune, and you’re on a device with a microphone (and really, what device today doesn’t have a microphone?) — and the site is still up (I haven’t looked lately) —, you can try going to midomi.com where you can search for songs by — believe it or not — humming them into your computer or other device’s microphone! :-o Good luck; hope this helps!
